{"id": "EUVD-2022-55421", "enisaUuid": "2df74e50-438b-3480-84e5-b5f24138a88f", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nHID: cp2112: prevent a buffer overflow in cp2112_xfer()\n\nSmatch warnings:\ndrivers/hid/hid-cp2112.c:793 cp2112_xfer() error: __memcpy()\n'data->block[1]' too small (33 vs 255)\ndrivers/hid/hid-cp2112.c:793 cp2112_xfer() error: __memcpy() 'buf' too\nsmall (64 vs 255)\n\nThe 'read_length' variable is provided by 'data->block[0]' which comes\nfrom user and it(read_length) can take a value between 0-255. Add an\nupper bound to 'read_length' variable to prevent a buffer overflow in\nmemcpy().", "datePublished": "2025-06-18T12:30:51", "dateUpdated": "2025-11-25T15:31:32", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/3af7d60e9a6c17d6d41c4341f8020511887d372d", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/519ff31a6ddd87aa4905bd9bf3b92e8b88801614", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/ebda3d6b004bb6127a66a616524a2de152302ca7", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8489a20ac481b08c0391608d81ed3796d373cfdf", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/e7028944e61014ae915e7fb74963d3835f2f761a", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/26e427ac85c2b8d0d108cc80b6de34d33e2780c4", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/381583845d19cb4bd21c8193449385f3fefa9caf", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50156"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50156"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "1a01b968-2894-35c8-8785-2acc2050ddb0", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 0"}, {"id": "41d46a1e-debf-32fc-a982-ac6e3a7fef97", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 4.19.256"}, {"id": "5b6ed396-8937-38c7-812a-2de89565bad2", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "542134c0375b5ca2b1d18490c02b8a20bfdd8d74 <519ff31a6ddd87aa4905bd9bf3b92e8b88801614"}, {"id": "5bd4a8ce-abf0-33ea-8b92-242504c37a7a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 5.4.211"}, {"id": "6688911f-26ed-3dbe-b788-1a